{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_277ed28e1ffeq6ogfgqGZBiS62","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d8812e9c1001PRjn1xXXK4LvuI","parts":[{"id":"prt_d8812f21b001qe0XmF3GNZ6Hcd","messageID":"msg_d8812e9c1001PRjn1xXXK4LvuI","sessionID":"ses_277ed28e1ffeq6ogfgqGZBiS62","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5853aa1b37de40f78064898f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: <h1 align=\"center\">\n2:   <picture>\n3:     <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_light.svg\">\n4:     <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_dark.svg\">\n5:     <img alt=\"EvoX Logo\" height=\"128\" width=\"500px\" src=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_dark.svg\">\n6:   </picture>\n7: </h1>\n8: \n9: <p align=\"center\">\n10:   <picture>\n11:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/pso_result.avif\">\n12:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/pso_result.gif\" alt=\"PSO Result\" height=\"150\">\n13:   </picture>\n14:   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n15:   <picture>\n16:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/rvea_result.avif\">\n17:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/rvea_result.gif\" alt=\"RVEA Result\" height=\"150\">\n18:   </picture>\n19:   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n20:   <picture>\n21:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/halfcheetah_200.avif\">\n22:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/halfcheetah_200.gif\" alt=\"HalfCheetah 200\" height=\"150\">\n23:   </picture>\n24: </p>\n25: \n26: \n27: <div align=\"center\">\n28:   <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2301.12457\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/arxiv-2212.05652-red\" alt=\"arXiv\"></a>\n29:   <a href=\"https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/readthedocs-docs-green?logo=readthedocs\" alt=\"Documentation\"></a>\n30:   <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/evox/\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/evox?logo=python\" alt=\"PyPI Version\"></a>\n31:   <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/evox/\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10+-orange?logo=python\" alt=\"Python Version\"></a>\n32:   <a href=\"https://discord.gg/Vbtgcpy7G4\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/discord-evox-%235865f2?logo=discord\" alt=\"Discord Server\"></a>\n33:   <a href=\"https://qm.qq.com/q/vTPvoMUGAw\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/QQ-297969717-%231db4f4?logo=tencentqq\" alt=\"QQ Group\"></a>\n34: </div>\n35: \n36: <p align=\"center\">\n37:   <a href=\"./README.md\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/English-f6f5f4\" alt=\"English README\"></a>\n38:   <a href=\"./README_ZH.md\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/中文-f6f5f4\" alt=\"中文 README\"></a>\n39: </p>\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: <h3 align=\"center\"> 🌟Distributed GPU-accelerated Framework for Scalable Evolutionary Computation🌟 </h3>\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: \n48: ## Table of Contents\n49: \n50: 1. [Overview](#Overview)\n51: 2. [Key Features](#key-features)\n52: 3. [Main Contents](#main-contents)\n53: 4. [Installation Guide](#installation-guide)\n54: 5. [Quick Start](#quick-start)\n55: 6. [Sister Projects](#sister-projects)\n56: 7. [Community & Support](#community--support)\n57: \n58: ## Overview\n59: \n60: EvoX is a distributed GPU-accelerated evolutionary computation framework compatible with **PyTorch**.  With a user-friendly programming model, it offers a comprehensive suite of **50+ Evolutionary Algorithms (EAs)** and a wide range of **100+ Benchmark Problems/Environments**. For more details, please refer to our [Paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2301.12457) and [Documentation](https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html) / [文档](https://evox.readthedocs.io/zh_CN/latest/index.html).\n61: \n62: > [!NOTE]\n63: > Users of the previous **JAX-based version** can access it on the **v0.9.0 branch**.\n64: \n65: \n66: ## Key Features\n67: \n68: ### 💻 High-Performance Computing\n69: \n70: #### 🚀 Ultra Performance\n71: - Supports acceleration on heterogeneous hardware, including both **CPUs** and **GPUs**, achieving over **100x speedups**.\n72: - Integrates **distributed workflows** that scale seamlessly across multiple nodes or devices.\n73: \n74: #### 🌐 All-in-One Solution\n75: - Includes **50+ algorithms** for a wide range of use cases, fully supporting **single- and multi-objective optimization**.\n76: - Provides a **hierarchical architecture** for complex tasks such as **meta learning**, **hyperparameter optimization**, and **neuroevolution**.\n77: \n78: #### 🛠️ Easy-to-Use Design\n79: - Fully compatible with **PyTorch** and its ecosystem, simplifying algorithmic development with a **tailored programming model**.\n80: - Ensures effortless setup with **one-click installation** for Windows users.\n81: \n82: \n83: ### 📊 Versatile Benchmarking\n84: \n85: #### 📚 Extensive Benchmark Suites\n86: - Features **100+ benchmark problems** spanning single-objective optimization, multi-objective optimization, and real-world engineering challenges.\n87: \n88: #### 🎮 Support for Physics Engines\n89: - Integrates seamlessly with physics engines like **Brax** and other popular frameworks for reinforcement learning.\n90: \n91: #### ⚙️ Customizable Problems\n92: - Provides an **encapsulated module** for defining and evaluating custom problems tailored to user needs, with seamless integration into real-world applications and datasets.\n93: \n94: \n95: ### 📈 Flexible Visualization\n96: \n97: #### 🔍 Ready-to-Use Tools\n98: - Offers a comprehensive set of **visualization tools** for analyzing evolutionary processes across various tasks.\n99: \n100: #### 🛠️ Customizable Modules\n101: - Enables users to integrate their own **visualization code**, allowing for tailored and flexible visualizations.\n102: \n103: #### 📂 Real-Time Data Streaming\n104: - Leverages the tailored **.exv format** to simplify and accelerate real-time data streaming.\n105: \n106: ## Main Contents\n107: \n108: <table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"8\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; text-align: left;\">\n109:   <thead>\n110:     <tr style=\"background-color: #f2f2f2;\">\n111:       <th>Category</th>\n112:       <th>Subcategory</th>\n113:       <th>Notable Algorithms / Benchmark Problems</th>\n114:     </tr>\n115:   </thead>\n116:   <tbody>\n117:     <tr>\n118:       <td rowspan=\"3\">Single-objective Optimization</td>\n119:       <td><b>Differential Evolution</b></td>\n120:       <td>CoDE, JaDE, SaDE, SHADE, IMODE, ...</td>\n121:     </tr>\n122:     <tr>\n123:       <td><b>Evolution Strategy</b></td>\n124:       <td>CMA-ES, PGPE, OpenES, CR-FM-NES, xNES, ...</td>\n125:     </tr>\n126:     <tr>\n127:       <td><b>Particle Swarm Optimization</b></td>\n128:       <td>FIPS, CSO, CPSO, CLPSO, SL-PSO, ...</td>\n129:     </tr>\n130:     <tr>\n131:       <td rowspan=\"3\">Multi-objective Optimization</td>\n132:       <td><b>Dominance-based</b></td>\n133:       <td>NSGA-II, NSGA-III, SPEA2, BiGE, KnEA, ...</td>\n134:     </tr>\n135:     <tr>\n136:       <td><b>Decomposition-based</b></td>\n137:       <td>MOEA/D, RVEA, t-DEA, MOEAD-M2M, EAG-MOEAD, ...</td>\n138:     </tr>\n139:     <tr>\n140:       <td><b>Indicator-based</b></td>\n141:       <td>IBEA, HypE, SRA, MaOEA-IGD, AR-MOEA, ...</td>\n142:     </tr>\n143:     <tr>\n144:       <td rowspan=\"2\">Benchmark Problems / Environments</td>\n145:       <td><b>Numerical</b></td>\n146:       <td>DTLZ, LSMOP, MaF, ZDT, CEC'22, ...</td>\n147:     </tr>\n148:     <tr>\n149:       <td><b>Neuroevolution / RL</b></td>\n150:       <td>Brax, TorchVision Dataset, ...</td>\n151:     </tr>\n152:   </tbody>\n153: </table>\n154: \n155: For a comprehensive list and detailed descriptions of all algorithms, please check the [Algorithms API](https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/apidocs/evox/evox.algorithms.html), and for benchmark problems/environments, refer to the [Problems API](https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/apidocs/evox/evox.problems.html).\n156: \n157: \n158: ## Installation Guide\n159: \n160: Install `evox` with default feature sets via `pip`:\n161: \n162: ```bash\n163: pip install \"evox[default]\"\n164: ```\n165: \n166: Install the latest version from the source code for testing or development:\n167: \n168: ```bash\n169: git clone https://github.com/EMI-Group/evox.git\n170: cd evox\n171: pip install -e .\n172: ```\n173: \n174: > [!TIP]\n175: > Windows users can use the [win-install.bat](https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/_downloads/796714545d73f0b52e921d885369323d/win-install.bat) script for installation.\n176: \n177: ## Quick Start\n178: \n179: Here are some examples to get you started with EvoX:\n180: \n181: ### Single-objective Optimization\n182: \n183: Solve the Ackley problem using the PSO algorithm:\n184: \n185: ```python\n186: import torch\n187: from evox.algorithms import PSO\n188: from evox.problems.numerical import Ackley\n189: from evox.workflows import StdWorkflow, EvalMonitor\n190: \n191: # torch.set_default_device(\"cuda\") # Uncomment this line if you want to use GPU by default\n192: \n193: algorithm = PSO(pop_size=100, lb=-32 * torch.ones(10), ub=32 * torch.ones(10))\n194: problem = Ackley()\n195: monitor = EvalMonitor()\n196: workflow = StdWorkflow(algorithm, problem, monitor)\n197: workflow.init_step()\n198: for i in range(100):\n199:     workflow.step()\n200: \n201: monitor.plot() # or monitor.plot().show() if you are using headless mode\n202: ```\n203: \n204: <details>\n205:   <summary>Example Output</summary>\n206: \n207:   <picture>\n208:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/1-single-objective-output.avif\">\n209:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/1-single-objective-output.png\">\n210:   </picture>\n211: \n212: </details>\n213: \n214: ### Multi-objective Optimization\n215: \n216: Solve the DTLZ2 problem using the RVEA algorithm:\n217: \n218: ```python\n219: import torch\n220: from evox.algorithms import RVEA\n221: from evox.problems.numerical import DTLZ2\n222: from evox.workflows import StdWorkflow, EvalMonitor\n223: \n224: # torch.set_default_device(\"cuda\") # Uncomment this line if you want to use GPU by default\n225: \n226: prob = DTLZ2(m=2)\n227: pf = prob.pf()\n228: algo = RVEA(\n229:     pop_size=100,\n230:     n_objs=2,\n231:     lb=-torch.zeros(12),\n232:     ub=torch.ones(12)\n233: )\n234: monitor = EvalMonitor()\n235: workflow = StdWorkflow(algo, prob, monitor)\n236: workflow.init_step()\n237: for i in range(100):\n238:     workflow.step()\n239: \n240: monitor.plot() # or monitor.plot().show() if you are using headless mode\n241: ```\n242: \n243: <details>\n244:   <summary>Example Output</summary>\n245: \n246:   <picture>\n247:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/2-multi-objective-output.avif\">\n248:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/2-multi-objective-output.png\">\n249:   </picture>\n250: \n251: </details>\n252: \n253: ### Neuroevolution\n254: \n255: Evolving a simple MLP model to solve the Brax HalfCheetah environment:\n256: \n257: ```python\n258: import torch\n259: import torch.nn as nn\n260: from evox.algorithms import PSO\n261: from evox.problems.neuroevolution.brax import BraxProblem\n262: from evox.utils import ParamsAndVector\n263: from evox.workflows import EvalMonitor, StdWorkflow\n264: \n265: # torch.set_default_device(\"cuda\") # Uncomment this line if you want to use GPU by default\n266: \n267: class SimpleMLP(nn.Module):\n268:     def __init__(self):\n269:         super().__init__()\n270:         # observation space is 17-dim, action space is 6-dim.\n271:         self.features = nn.Sequential(nn.Linear(17, 8), nn.Tanh(), nn.Linear(8, 6))\n272: \n273:     def forward(self, x):\n274:         return torch.tanh(self.features(x))\n275: \n276: # Initialize the MLP model\n277: model = SimpleMLP()\n278: adapter = ParamsAndVector(dummy_model=model)\n279: # Set the population size\n280: POP_SIZE = 1024\n281: # Get the bound of the PSO algorithm\n282: model_params = dict(model.named_parameters())\n283: pop_center = adapter.to_vector(model_params)\n284: lb = torch.full_like(pop_center, -5)\n285: ub = torch.full_like(pop_center, 5)\n286: # Initialize the PSO, and you can also use any other algorithms\n287: algorithm = PSO(pop_size=POP_SIZE, lb=lb, ub=ub)\n288: # Initialize the Brax problem\n289: problem = BraxProblem(\n290:     policy=model,\n291:     env_name=\"halfcheetah\",\n292:     max_episode_length=1000,\n293:     num_episodes=3,\n294:     pop_size=POP_SIZE,\n295: )\n296: # set an monitor, and it can record the top 3 best fitnesses\n297: monitor = EvalMonitor(topk=3)\n298: # Initiate an workflow\n299: workflow = StdWorkflow(\n300:     algorithm=algorithm,\n301:     problem=problem,\n302:     monitor=monitor,\n303:     opt_direction=\"max\",\n304:     solution_transform=adapter,\n305: )\n306: workflow.init_step()\n307: for i in range(50):\n308:     workflow.step()\n309: \n310: monitor.plot() # or monitor.plot().show() if you are using headless mode\n311: ```\n312: \n313: <details>\n314:   <summary>Example Output</summary>\n315: \n316:   <picture>\n317:     <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/3-neuroevolution-output.avif\">\n318:     <img src=\"docs/source/_static/3-neuroevolution-output.gif\">\n319:   </picture>\n320: \n321: </details>\n322: \n323: > [!NOTE]\n324: > For comprehensive guidance, please visit our [Documentation](https://evox.readthedocs.io/en/latest/), where you'll find detailed installation steps, tutorials, practical examples, and complete API references.\n325: \n326: ## Sister Projects\n327: - **EvoRL**: GPU-accelerated framework for Evolutionary Reinforcement Learning. Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evorl).\n328: - **EvoGP**: GPU-accelerated framework for Genetic Programming. Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evogp).\n329: - **EvoMO**: GPU-accelerated library for Evolutionary Multiobjective Optimization (EMO).Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evomo).\n330: - **TensorNEAT**: Tensorized NeuroEvolution of Augmenting Topologies (NEAT) for GPU Acceleration. Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/tensorneat).\n331: - **TensorACO**: Tensorized Ant Colony Optimization (ACO) for GPU Acceleration. Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/tensoraco).\n332: - **EvoXBench**: A real-world benchmark platform for solving various optimization problems, such as Neural Architecture Search (NAS). It operates without the need for GPUs/PyTorch/TensorFlow and supports multiple programming environments. Check out [here](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evoxbench).\n333: \n334: Stay tuned - more exciting developments are on the way!  ✨\n335: \n336: ## Community & Support\n337: \n338: - Join discussions on the [GitHub Discussion Board](https://github.com/EMI-Group/evox/discussions).\n339: - Connect via [Discord](https://discord.gg/Vbtgcpy7G4) or QQ group (ID: 297969717).\n340: - Visit [Offical Website](https://evox.group/).\n341: \n342: ## Citing EvoX\n343: \n344: If EvoX contributes to your research, please cite it:\n345: \n346: ```bibtex\n347: @article{evox,\n348:   title = {{EvoX}: {A} {Distributed} {GPU}-accelerated {Framework} for {Scalable} {Evolutionary} {Computation}},\n349:   author = {Huang, Beichen and Cheng, Ran and Li, Zhuozhao and Jin, Yaochu and Tan, Kay Chen},\n350:   journal = {IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation},\n351:   year = 2024,\n352:   doi = {10.1109/TEVC.2024.3388550}\n353: }\n354: ```\n355: \n356: ## License Notice\n357: \n358: EvoX is licensed under the **GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)**. For full terms and conditions, please refer to the [LICENSE](./LICENSE) file.\n359: \n360: <!--\n361: ## Star History\n362: [![Star History Chart](https://api.star-history.com/svg?repos=EMI-Group/evox&type=Date)](https://star-history.com/#EMI-Group/evox&Date)\n363: -->\n\n(End of file - total 363 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<h1 align=\"center\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_light.svg\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_dark.svg\">\n    <img alt=\"EvoX Logo\" height=\"128\" width=\"500px\" src=\"docs/source/_static/evox_brand_dark.svg\">\n  </picture>\n</h1>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <picture>\n    <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/pso_result.avif\">\n    <img src=\"docs/source/_static/pso_result.gif\" alt=\"PSO Result\" height=\"150\">\n  </picture>\n  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n  <picture>\n    <source type=\"image/avif\" srcset=\"docs/source/_static/rvea_result.avif\">\n    <img src=\"docs/source/_static/rvea_result.gif\" alt=\"RVEA Result\" height=\"150\">\n  </picture>\n  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n  <picture>","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1776104436683,"end":1776104436695}}}]}
